<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4001907>
    dc:description "Figure 51. Development site of Lonchaea sylvatica and Stegana coleoptrata, sooty fungi under lenticels of Betula bark, from a cut branch." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4001907/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4001909>
    dc:description "Figure 52. Stegana coleoptrata, preserved larva, thorax and head, head to the right, lateral view, length 1.3 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4001909/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4001911>
    dc:description "Figure 53. Stegana coleoptrata, thorax and head cleared in KOH, lateral view, head to the right, as = anterior spiracle; ms = mesothorax; mt = metathorax; os = oral sclerite; pro = prothorax; ps = pseudocephalon." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4001911/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4001913>
    dc:description "Figure 54. Lonchaea sylvatica, still from Film 19 showing small, sclerotised part of the oral plate (os), appearing below the inclined mandibular hooks (m), ventral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4001913/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4001815>
    dc:description "Figures 6. Polyporivora picta, head skeleton from a puparium. (A) Lateral view, labial teeth to the right, length 0.6 mm; (B) apical view of labial teeth." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4001815/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4001827>
    dc:description "Figures 12. Melangyna cincta, preserved larva. (A) Prothorax and apex of head skeleton, apico-ventral view; (B) prothorax and apex of head skeleton, lateral view; (C) drawing of apical end of the head skeleton, lateral view. a = antenna; c = connecting tissue; lb = labrum; lm = labium; m = mandible; ma = postero-ventral muscle attachment apodeme; os = labial sclerite; ts = triangular sclerite." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4001827/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4001847>
    dc:description "Figure 22. Silba fumosa, mesothorax folding over prothorax during locomotion, lateral view, still from Film 9." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4001847/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4001849>
    dc:description "Figures 23. Coelopha frigida, stills from a film. (A) Mandibles gripping a substrate at the end of a peristaltic wave. (B) Prothorax folded over the pseudocephalon during the next locomotory wave." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4001849/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4001835>
    dc:description "Figure 16. Calliphora vomitoria, drawing of the left hand mandible, dental sclerite and tendons, outside lateral view, length 0.4 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4001835/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4001837>
    dc:description "Figure 17. Calliphora vomitoria, drawing of the posterior face of the right hand mandible, elevator tendon on the upper margin and ridge of the hinge joint with the apex of the intermediate sclerite (Figure 18) across the lower margin, height 0.1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4001837/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4001839>
    dc:description "Figure 18. Calliphora vomitoria, drawing of the anterior face of the intermediate sclerite with inclined grooves of the hinge joint formed with a ridge on the posterior face of the mandible (Figure 17), maximum width 0.2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4001839/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4001873>
    dc:description "Figure 35. Clusia flava, preserved larva, lateral view, head to the right, length 8.7 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4001873/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4001861>
    dc:description "Figure 29. Lonchaea hackmani, prothorax unfolding during a lunge, still from Film 13." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4001861/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4001863>
    dc:description "Figure 30. Neophyllomyza acyglossa, prothorax unfolding during a lunge, still from a film." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4001863/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4001885>
    dc:description "Figures 41. Head skeletons of phytophagous species, lateral views, mandibles to the left. (A) Tephritis vespertina, length 0.3 mm; (B) Acidia cognata, length 0.6 mm; (C) Chaetostomella cylindrica, length 0.6 mm; (D) Botanophila seneciella, length 0.7 mm. Botanophila seneciella, drawing of mandible and intermediate sclerite: (E) lateral view with muscle tendons; (F) ventral view; (G) Pegomya solennis, length 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4001885/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

